elements.description:
The datetime components rely on [Moment.js](https://momentjs.com/) and [Moment Timezone](https://momentjs.com/timezone/).

#### Usage

    <px-datetime-picker
      collapse-at="720">
    </px-datetime-picker>


#### Styling
The following custom properties are available for styling. Please also refer to px-forms-design and px-buttons-design for additional style variables used by this component.

Custom property | Description
:----------------|:-------------
`--px-datetime-picker-background-color` | Background color for the panel
`--px-datetime-picker-btn-container-background-color` | Background color for the button wrapper When `fillContainer` is true
`--px-datetime-picker-border-color` | Border color for the panel
`--px-datetime-picker-z-index` | The z-index of the container

properties.name: momentObj
properties.description: Moment value with the date or time to display.  Will be parsed according to the moment format. (See momentFormat property.)

properties.name: _tempMomentObj
properties.description:
temporary moment object used for validation and display. This
object should be used by subcomponents when we want to "try"
a value and see the result of validation AND/OR give us the
ability to rollback (cancel) or apply

properties.name: showButtons
properties.description: Whether to show Apply and Cancel buttons in the components

properties.name: containerType
properties.description: An optional type set on the px-overlay-container and px-overlay-content to associate specific overlay-contents with their container

properties.name: showTimeZone
properties.description:
Can be set to show the timezone in the field. values:
- 'dropdown': shows the time zone as a dropdown which the user can use to
select a different time zone. Only contains a subset of all time zones
- 'extendedDropdown': shows the time zone as a dropdown which the user can use to
select a different time zone. Contains all existing time zones (588)
- 'text': shows the time zone as text, non editable
- 'abbreviatedText': shows the time zone as an abbreviated text, non editable (such as PST, EST...)

properties.name: hideTime
properties.description: Doesn't display the time in the field and panel(if applicable)

properties.name: dateFormat
properties.description: Moment format used for the date

properties.name: timeFormat
properties.description: Moment format used for the time

properties.name: required
properties.description:
Boolean stating if the picker is required.
Picker will become invalid if a user leaves
the picker empty when required is true.

properties.name: opened
properties.description: Reflects if datetime-picker container is visible.

properties.name: fieldIsValid
properties.description: Reflects if the field is valid.

properties.name: fillContainer
properties.description:
If false, the contents will open in a panel.

If true, the contents will fill the window
or an element defined by the `fitIntoElement`.

properties.name: _fillContainer
properties.description:
Used to toggle fillContainer from iron-media-query.
Without a separate variable fillContainer would never be
true with a screen size larger then the value of collapseAt

properties.name: fitIntoElement
properties.description:
The element that the contents will fully expand into
when it is opened.

`fillContainer` must be true in order for this property to work

properties.name: _fitIntoElement
properties.description:
Used to toggle `fitIntoElement` from iron-media-query.
Without separate variable each time the screen was
smaller than collpasAt the `fitIntoElement` would
get over written.

properties.name: collapseAt
properties.description:
The width below which the datetime picker will collapse into a mobile
friendly view. This will supersede any other configuration if set.
Use a number (e.g. `450`) which will be converted to a
pixel value (e.g. '450px').

If no value is provided, the datetime picker will not collapse
automatically.

properties.name: collapsed
properties.description: True if screen size is smaller than the `collapseAt` value

properties.name: _belowCollapseSize
properties.description: Output of iron-media-query

properties.name: hoist
properties.description: Specifies if the dropdown content should get hoisted to a container in order to escape its current stacking context

methods.name: attached
methods.description:
We don't need to listen to the time field from the calendar
sense it only updates the temp moment but should never trigger an
actual validation

element. This is the imperative equivalent of declaring a keybinding
in the `keyBindings` prototype property.

methods.description: When called, will remove all imperatively-added key bindings.

methods.description: Returns true if a keyboard event matches `eventString`.

methods.name: _preserveTime
methods.description:
Copies the time in toPreserve to dest and returns dest.
used in `px-calendar-picker`, `px-datetime-picker`, and `px-datetime-range-panel`

methods.name: _localeChanged
methods.description: Make sure the moment obj pick up the possibly new moment locale

methods.name: _timeZoneChanged
methods.description: Makes sure the moment object reflects the right timezone.

methods.name: _applyTempMoment
methods.description: Applies value of temp moment to public momentObj

methods.name: _rollbackTempMoment
methods.description: Rollback value of temp moment to use public momentObj

methods.name: _localeChangedTemp
methods.description: Make sure the moment obj pick up the possibly new moment locale

methods.name: _timeZoneChangedTemp
methods.description: Makes sure the moment object reflects the right timezone.

methods.name: focus
methods.description: Propagate focus from the host to px-datetime-field

methods.name: _onEsc
methods.description:
Rolls back temp moment to the momentObj.
Closes panel

methods.name: _onEnter
methods.description: Runs validation

methods.name: _handleTap
methods.description: If the calendar is open and the dropdown is selected, close the calendar

methods.name: _tempMomentChanged
methods.description:
Ran when the momentObjs for field or content have been updated.
If it is from the field, then apply the momentObj.
If it is from the content and we have no buttons, then apply the momentObj.
Else, wait for button events.

methods.name: _validateCalendarMoment
methods.description:
Apply temp moment if the dropdown is opened and
the field is valid

methods.name: _buttonClicked
methods.description:
submit: validate values
cancel: rolls back temp moment to the momentObj &closes panel

methods.name: _iconClicked
methods.description: Opens content

methods.name: _processClose
methods.description:
If opened is false and showButtons true
then cancel selection

methods.name: _getCollapseQuery
methods.description: Return the collapseAt value with px after it

methods.name: _collapseQueryIsValid
methods.description: Double checks that the collapseAt value is valid

methods.name: _handleBelowCollapseSizeChanged
methods.description:
If the window is smaller than the `collapseAt` value
set panel to fill the whole window

If the window is larger than the `collapseAt` value
reset `_fillContainer` & `_fitIntoElement` to their
original values

methods.name: _syncFillContainer
methods.description: Sync external fillConatiner with internal _fillConatiner

methods.name: _syncFitIntoElement
methods.description:
Sync external fitIntoElement with internal _fitIntoElement.
Make sure `_fitIntoElement` isn't over written if
`_belowCollapseSize` is true

methods.name: _returnField
methods.description: Return field node
